word_mean_info__list.difference: 指物品的价格超过了它本身所值，或超过了购买者的支付能力。
侧重指要价过高，或远高于公道、合理的价格，其反义词是cheap。
指物品价格高，通常是因物品稀少或珍贵所致。

word_group.brief_definition: 昂贵的设备；昂贵的仪器
昂贵的模型；昂贵的型号

bilingual.source: This is a small but expensive clothing store.
bilingual.target: 这是一个小而昂贵的服装店。

bilingual.source: On the other hand, it's an expensive way to communicate.
bilingual.target: 另一方面，这是一种昂贵的沟通方式。

bilingual.source: I cannot understand spending all this money on expensive research.
bilingual.target: 我无法理解花这么多钱在昂贵的研究上。

bilingual.source: When you want to buy something expensive, what do you do?
bilingual.target: 当你想买昂贵的东西时，你会怎么做？

bilingual.source: Wearing blue jeans, Gary stood in front of an expensive tailor's shop.
bilingual.target: 加里穿着蓝色牛仔裤站在一家昂贵的裁缝店前。

bilingual.source: This famous and expensive dish is especially popular in southern China.
bilingual.target: 这种著名且昂贵的菜在中国南方特别受欢迎。

bilingual.source: Although it is not necessary to wear expensive clothes, some people like to.
bilingual.target: 尽管没有必要穿昂贵的衣服，有些人喜欢这样。
他买了一辆昂贵的汽车。
她买了一条昂贵的项目。

list.abstract: expensive（英[ɪkˈspensɪv]，美[ɪkˈspensɪv]），英语单词，形容词，译为花钱多的；昂贵的。短语搭配有expensive equipment（昂贵的设备）。例句为“But electric cars themselves are more expensive.（但是电动车本身更贵。）” 该单词的比较级为more expensive，最高级为most expensive，形容词性近义词为rich、dear、costly，相关反义词为cheap。

yingyinNormal.en: But having expensive things isn't the way to do it. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是拥有昂贵的东西并不是融入的方法。好吧。

yingyinNormal.en: What you're buying here are the ingredients for very expensive urine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你买这么多，就是买的一堆昂贵的尿液原料。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, then, it seems that your great big expensive machine doesn't work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，看起来你这伟大又昂贵的机器不起作用。

yingyinNormal.en: We want to buy a really expensive meal. We don't want to eat pork rolls at a stall, even with apple sauce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们就想吃一顿昂贵的大餐，我们不想去小吃摊吃什么猪肉卷，有苹果酱也不要。

yingyinNormal.en: Wow! Look at that. The car is on fire, yet somehow its expensive paint job is protected by the Miracle Wax.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你瞧瞧，车子起火了，可是它那昂贵的烤漆却被奇迹蜡保护得毫发无伤。

yingyinNormal.en: So, I'm gonna need to have that back. But, in exchange I'm willing to trade you this beautiful, more expensive ring.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过我愿意拿这枚美丽的，更昂贵的戒指和你交换。

yingyinNormal.en: To create a nationwide web of tracks, the Federal Government launched one of the most ambitious and expensive infrastructure projects in human history.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为制造全国铁路线的网络，联邦政府启动人类史上最具野心，也是最昂贵的基础设施计划。

yingyinNormal.en: It looks like someone else's expensive gold locket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过貌似这贵重的金吊坠是别人的啊

yingyinNormal.en: Were they expensive? Didn't cost a thing. I made them myself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这东西贵吗？一分钱没花，我自己做的。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe you should talk to a therapist about this. Too expensive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这事你去找咨询师聊聊吧。太贵了。

yingyinNormal.en: They found a plan with coverage they liked and it was way less expensive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们找到了一个他们想要的方案，这一方案不是那么贵。

yingyinNormal.en: You walk in and the prices stun you, because they are much more expensive than Dunkin' Donuts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 走进店里价目表让你惊讶，比邓肯甜甜圈店贵很多。

yingyinNormal.en: Ball! Oh, no, that's not a ball. No. No, no, no. That's a criminally expensive Santangelo bowl.
yingyinNormal.zh: 球球！不，那不是球球。不不不，那是个贵到吓死人的圣安杰洛牌玻璃碗。

yingyinNormal.en: I feel like there was a fish in that last one. Yup. Oh, no, it's the expensive one! That's so me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我感觉最后那下里面有鱼。没错，惨了，是贵的那只！标准的我，净挑贵的。

yingyinNormal.en: Sounds expensive. Okay, well, I may have gone a bit overboard, but you can't put a price on safety.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听起来就是贵货啊。好吧，我可能有点太舍得了，可安全是无价之宝啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Why? This house is too big for us. You're going to school eventually. It's too expensive. I'm done.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么？这房子给我们住太大了，你迟早有一天会去上大学，这太贵了，我承担不起。

yingyinNormal.en: Look, I know that it's more expensive than their one bedrooms, but you like, you like it, right? Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我知道这种双卧房型比一体式房型要贵，但是你喜欢，你喜欢对不对？对。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, that's the point of an Oxford education. Isn't it, Dad? It's the expensive alternative to a dinner dance.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这不就是牛津教育的本质吗 爸爸? 不就是花大钱去舞会跳个舞吗?

yingyinNormal.en: They came to my dad and they told him to do some creative accounting. Make it way too expensive to ever go back.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们来找我爸，让他在账目中做些手脚，使得返回月球花费太高。

yingyinNormal.en: What an excellent room you have, sir. Such expensive furnishings. I do hope you intend to stay here, Mr Bingley.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的屋子多可爱啊，先生。贵重的家具。我非常希望你能留在这，彬格莱先生。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_usage.usage:
expensive意为“昂贵的，费用巨大的”，不可与price连用。
示例：这裙子太贵了。
误 The price of this dress is too expensive.
正 The price of this dress is too high.
正 This dress is too expensive.

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指物品价格高, 通常是因物品稀少或珍贵所致。
侧重指要价过高, 或远高于公道、合理的价格, 其反义词是 cheap。
指物品的价格超过了它本身所值, 或超过了购买者的支付能力。
